==English==

===Etymology===

'''malevolence'''

# From the latin word ''[[malevolentiam]]'', derived from ''[[malevolens]]'' ([[malevolent]]).

===Noun===
'''malevolence'''

# [[hostile|Hostile]] attitude and feeling. "'''To show someone malevolence'''". "'''He said it with malevolence'''".
# [[ill-will|Ill-will]], [[malice]], [[spite]]. 

